<item>
            <title>[FLINK-36378] type extraction problem between java BigDecimal and sql decimal</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-36378</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;add following to&#160;ValueDataTypeConverterTest&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;of(new BigDecimal(&quot;0.000&quot;), DataTypes.DECIMAL(4, 3))&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;org.apache.flink.table.api.ValidationException:&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
Decimal scale must be between 0 and the precision 1 (both inclusive).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;spark&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;0.000 -&amp;gt; decimal(3, 3)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;calcite&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;0.000 -&amp;gt; decimal(4, 3)&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;so follow the calcite&lt;/p&gt;</description>
