                            <comment id="17885189" author="jackylau" created="Fri, 27 Sep 2024 01:46:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=twalthr&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;twalthr&quot;&gt;twalthr&lt;/a&gt; , will you have time to have a look?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17885288" author="JIRAUSER305836" created="Fri, 27 Sep 2024 09:35:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There is already a PR about this issue: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/24981&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/24981&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And I think we need to first define the meaning of &lt;tt&gt;precision&lt;/tt&gt;. &lt;br/&gt;
If we follow Calcite, what does it mean when &lt;tt&gt;scale = precision&lt;/tt&gt;, considering the DecimalType constructor allows &lt;tt&gt;scale &amp;lt;= precision&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;WDYT? &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=empathy87&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;empathy87&quot;&gt;empathy87&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=lincoln.86xy&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;lincoln.86xy&quot;&gt;lincoln.86xy&lt;/a&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17885610" author="jingge" created="Sat, 28 Sep 2024 19:56:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;afaik, precision must be greater than scale according to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/blob/6633719c728526a08344645e0a844f27d25629f4/flink-table/flink-table-common/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/table/types/logical/DecimalType.java#L74&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/blob/6633719c728526a08344645e0a844f27d25629f4/flink-table/flink-table-common/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/table/types/logical/DecimalType.java#L74&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
